OL,3,GYorkshire & Humber
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FDry and largely sunny start.
OL,6,FCloud then builds from the southwest
OL,7,Fthrough the day, with brighter spells
OL,8,Fbecoming more limited through the
OL,9,Fafternoon. Many parts staying dry, but
OL,10,Fa few outbreaks of rain possible,
OL,11,Fheaviest across the Pennines. Turning
OL,12,Fbreezy.
OL,13,
OL,14,CTonight:FStaying cloudy and breezy
OL,15,Fovernight, with further outbreaks of
OL,16,Frain. Heavier and more persistent rain
OL,17,Fspreads northeast during the early
OL,18,Fhours of Wednesday, clearing around
OL,19,Fdawn.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
